    {
      "type": "add",
      "item": {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "id": "5f41ad98-7238-4a16-96cb-02fa01bd1f60",
        "text": "Patent pools do not eliminate risk, they only temper it.  Patent holders (including other patent pools) outside the pool can still create cost and risk for the industry.  While it is rare for a patent pool to indemnify licensees,[http://intellectualpats.com/patent-pools-what-are-they-what-are-their-uses-and-their-benefits/ Patent Pools: What Are They, What Are Their Uses and Their Benefits?] a pool does help to assure a common interest will emerge should one member be accused of infringement by a third party.  Flaws in the design of the pool's governance can create the risk that one member can break the common cause of the group.  Examples of well-known such cases include the [[MPEG-2]], [[MPEG-4 Part 2]] and H.264 ([[H.264/MPEG-4 AVC]]) video coding standards, and the [[DVD6C]] pool. The MPEG-2 patent pool ([[MPEG-2#Patent pool]]) has also been criticized because by 2015 more than 90% of the MPEG-2 patents will have expired but as long as there are one or more active patents in the MPEG-2 patent pool in either the country of manufacture or the country of sale the MPEG-2 license agreement requires that licensees pay a license fee that does not change based on the number of patents that have expired.[http://www.businesswire.com/news/home/20130509005972/en/Patent-Pools-Create-Anticompetitive-Effects-Report-Finds Patent Pools May Create Anticompetitive Effects, New Report Finds][http://dailycaller.com/2013/05/13/consumer-tech-rip-off-from-patent-pools/ Consumer tech rip-off from patent pools][https://www.forbes.com/sites/bretswanson/2013/04/30/mpeg-la-shows-need-to-rebuild-ip-foundations/ MPEG-LA Shows Need to Rebuild IP Foundations][http://www.foxnews.com/opinion/2013/03/18/america-patent-system-is-all-wrong-for-todays-high-tech-world/ America's patent system is all wrong for todayâ€™s high-tech world][http://www.mpegla.com/main/programs/M2/Pages/License.aspx MPEG-2 License Agreement]"
